{"parse":{"title":"Chak-pur","pageid":41776880,"revid":774700282,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Chak-pur</b> are the traditional tools used in <a href=\"/wiki/Tibetan_people\" title=\"Tibetan people\">Tibetan</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Sandpainting\" title=\"Sandpainting\">sandpainting</a> to produce <i><a href=\"/wiki/Mandala\" title=\"Mandala\">mandalas</a></i>. They are conically shaped metal funnels and often have ridges down the sides. Normally about 12\u201318 inches (300\u2013460&#160;mm) in length, they taper to a fine point and are made with varying diameter holes at the end in order to disperse the sand in a controlled way. A Tibetan monk will usually tap glide a piece of wood over the ridges in order to slowly allow the sand to emerge through the hole through the vibrations created.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chak-pur&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.mysticalartsoftibet.org/mandala.htm\">\"Mandala Sand Painting\"</a>. Drepung Loseling Monastery<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">16 August</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Mandala+Sand+Painting&amp;rft.pub=Drepung+Loseling+Monastery&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mysticalartsoftibet.org%2Fmandala.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChak-pur\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:White_Palace_of_the_Potala.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/White_Palace_of_the_Potala.jpg/40px-White_Palace_of_the_Potala.jpg\" width=\"40\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/White_Palace_of_the_Potala.jpg/60px-White_Palace_of_the_Potala.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/White_Palace_of_the_Potala.jpg/80px-White_Palace_of_the_Potala.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/Tibet\" title=\"Tibet\">Tibet</a>-related article is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Chak-pur&amp;action=edit\">expanding it</a>.</i><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\" style=\"position: absolute; right: 15px; display: none;\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Tibet-stub\" title=\"Template:Tibet-stub\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Tibet-stub\" title=\"Template talk:Tibet-stub\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Tibet-stub&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1239\nCached time: 20180907212013\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.072 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.106 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count